com.qualcomm.snapdragon.sdk.location

Class IZatManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qualcomm.snapdragon.sdk.location.IZatManager

  • public class IZatManager
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides location based services and feature query. 
     Usage example of feature query:

 public class MyAcitivty extends Activity {
     private IZatManager mIZatManager;
     private IZatLciService mIZatLciService;
     private boolean mHasQcIndoor;
     private boolean mHasQcGeofence;
     private boolean mHasQcUlp;

     public void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
         super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);

         Context context = gestApplicationContext();
         mHasQcIndoor = IZatManager.isFeatureSupported(context, FEATURE_BIT_PRECISE_INDOOR_POSITIONING);
         mHasQcGeofence = IZatManager.isFeatureSupported(context, FEATURE_BIT_OPTIMAL_GEOFENCING);
         mHasQcUlp = IZatManager.isFeatureSupported(context, FEATURE_BIT_OPTIMAL_CRITERIA_POSITIONING);
         mIZatManager = mIZatManager.getInstance(context);
         mIZatLciService = mIZatManager.getLciService();
     }

     public void onStart() {
         super.onStart();

         if (mIZatManager.isEulaAccepted()) {
             if (mHasQcIndoor) {
                 // need to launch Location Settings
                 startActivity(new Intent("android.settings.LOCATION_SOURCE_SETTINGS"));
             }
         }
     }
 }

      • PERMISSION_ACCESS_LCI

        public static final java.lang.String PERMISSION_ACCESS_LCI
        Permission required to access LCI service. To call LCI service developers must add the permission "android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION" to the application's AndroidManifest.xml file, as shown below:
             <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION" />

      • isEulaAccepted

        public boolean isEulaAccepted()
        Checks if IZat EULA is accepted by user
        Returns:
        ture, if this is Qualcomm powered device and EULA is accepted by user;
        false, if this is not Qualcomm powered device or EULA is not accepted by user. In the second case, Settings app can be launched to user, which would promp to user to review and possibly accept EULA.

      • getLciService

        public IZatLciService getLciService()
                             throws IZatIllegalArgumentException,
                                    IZatServiceUnavailableException,
                                    IZatSecurityException
        Get a IZatLciService interface of LCI service.

        This api requires IZat LCI service be present; otherwise a IZatServiceUnavailableException
        will be thrown. It also requires the application be granted PERMISSION_ACCESS_LCI;
        otherwise a IZatSecurityException will be thrown.

        This api may take as long as several seconds. It is recommended not to call this api in main thread.

        Returns:
        A IZatLciService interface.
        Throws:
        IZatIllegalArgumentException
        IZatServiceUnavailableException
        IZatSecurityException
